body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello! Thank you for contacting ABC Auto Solutions. My name is Jacob Sanders. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hello, Jacob! My name is Margaret Ramirez.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Margaret! Could you please provide me with your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure. It's five five five, three three three, two two two two.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Margaret. Can you also provide your email address?

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Perfect! We have received your contact details. Is there anything specific you would like assistance with today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm just looking for information on the latest car models available in your inventory.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: I'll be glad to help with that, Margaret. Thank you for your time and interest in ABC Auto Solutions. Have a great day!

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Thank you, Jacob. Have a great day too!
